-- Russia's Mail.Ru Q1 sales up 25 pct, keeps full-year guidance
-- By Maria Kiselyova
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 02:09AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, April 24 (Reuters) - Russian internet group Mail.Ru <MAILRq.L> on Thursday confirmed its full-year revenue growth guidance as it reported a 25 percent rise in first-quarter sales to 7.8 billion roubles ($218.5 million).

The company, controlled by Russia's richest man Alisher Usmanov, said in February it expected revenue growth of 22-24 percent and an EBITDA margin of 53-54 percent in 2014. [ID:nL6N0LO378]